President Biden wrote an op-ed in which he announced new actions being taken by his administration to implement the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act and address gun violence. He honored the lives lost in the Buffalo and Uvalde shootings and emphasized the need for Congress to take additional action to save lives. The President highlighted the executive actions he has already taken and called for Congress to ban assault weapons, require secure firearm storage, implement universal background checks, and repeal gun manufacturers' immunity from liability. He also urged governors and state legislators to take steps to reduce gun violence. President Biden discussed the progress made with the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act and outlined further actions his administration is taking to maximize its benefits. He emphasized the importance of building a coalition to demand additional gun safety legislation and invited law enforcement leaders to the White House to support an assault weapons ban. The President concluded by stressing the urgency of addressing gun violence and the need to protect future generations.